I would love to work on games for a living, but my last 2 attempts failed. It seems more like winning the lottery if your game is successful, regardless of how fun it is.<br /><br />I have since given up and moved back into back-end systems development and testing and am doing quite well for myself again.<br />It just seems like a ton of work with very little return, other than the fact that you get to work on games.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=45">drk421</a> — Fri May 02, 2014 6:06 pm</p><hr />
